      "content": "For hidden boundary issues, the city's inspectors rely heavily on precise surveying and site plans, not just street-level appearances. If an unrecorded structural overlap is discovered during an inspection, it will be flagged as non-conforming construction, which is a serious finding. The best way to resolve this is proactive communication; you should engage the city planning department early to request a survey and discuss a formal modification or variance application *before* an inspector finds it. This approach shows due diligence and prevents escalation into a legal dispute.",
